==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ship railway
<hw>Ship railway</hw>. <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An inclined railway running
into the water with a cradelike car on which a vessel may be drawn out
on land, as for repairs.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A railway on which to
transport vessels overland between bodies of water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ship-rigged</ent>⟦br⟧
